==English==
===Etymology===
Latin '''circus''', "ring, circle"
===Noun===
'''circus'''

#Company that travels around to give shows involving animals, [[clown]]s, etc., usually in a circular [[tent]]
#:''The circus will be in town next week.''
#Round open space in a town or city where multiple streets meet
#:''Piccadilly Circus in London is at the north end of Regent Street.''

===Related terms===
* [[circular]]
* [[circle]]

